laboratory_examinations.findings: A tubular structure in the expected region of the appendix measures up to 9 mm in caliber, highly suspicious for appendicitis. No evidence of abscess formation or free intraperitoneal air to suggest perforation. Prominent lymph nodes in the pericecal region, measuring up to 8 mm in the short axis, likely reactive. Small quantity of fluid seen within the right paracolic gutter. Small-to-moderate quantity of free fluid in the pelvis.
